age black mobility, to challenge narratives of racial authenticity, and to fight for racial and economic justice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Nov 2020) 0aBlues (Music)xHistory and criticism. 0aPerformance practice (Music)zSouthern StatesxHistoryy20th century. 7aMUSIC / Genres & Styles / Blues.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311071182040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822376316zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822376316423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822376316.jpg  a978-3-11-071182-0  DUK eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles